events.name: Washington Huskies at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Jake Browning and No. 5 Washington passed its final test of the regular season thanks to one nearly perfect quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 5 Washington tops No. 23 Washington State 45-17

headlines.description: C.J. Beathard threw three touchdown passes and Iowa pummeled No. 16 Nebraska 40-10 on Friday, knocking the Cornhuskers out of Big Ten title contention.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa tops No. 16 Nebraska 40-10, Wisconsin wins Big Ten West

video.headline: Beathard, Iowa come out on top on senior night

events.name: Boise State Broncos at Air Force Falcons

headlines.description: Air Force had a late goal-line stand, Tyler Weaver returned a blocked punt 11 yards for a touchdown and the Falcons beat No. 19 Boise State 27-20 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Goal-line stand lifts AFA to 27-20 win over No. 19 Boise St

headlines.description: In what might be Tom Herman's final game with No. 20 Houston , Riley Ferguson threw a 10-yard touchdown pass with 19 seconds left in a wild fourth quarter Friday to lift Memphis.
headlines.shortLinkText: Amid Herman rumors, No. 20 Houston loses to Memphis 48-44

events.name: Toledo Rockets at Western Michigan Broncos

headlines.description: Corey Davis and No. 21 Western Michigan wrapped up an undefeated regular season in style, routing Toledo 55-35 on Friday night to secure a berth next week in the MAC championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 21 WMU still unbeaten after 55-35 rout of Toledo

video.headline: Western Michigan running away with 27-yard TD

events.name: Northern Illinois Huskies at Kent State Golden Flashes

headlines.description: Joel Bouagnon ran for two touchdowns, Daniel Santacaterina and Jordan Huff each ran for scores, and Northern Illinois beat Kent State 31-21 in Friday's season finale for both teams.

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Jaylen Samuels ran for one touchdown and threw for another on a trick play, and North Carolina State held on to upset North Carolina 28-21 on Friday, earning bowl eligibility while also locking u
headlines.shortLinkText: Samuels, Dayes help NC State knock off Tar Heels 28-21

video.headline: Dayes busts through all the tackles for NC State TD

headlines.description: Drew Lock completed 16 of 26 passes for 268 yards and a touchdown, and Missouri scored 21 unanswered second-half points in a 28-24 victory over Arkansas 28-24 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Missouri defeats Arkansas 28-24 behind big second half

events.name: Buffalo Bulls at Bowling Green Falcons

headlines.description: Fred Coppet rushed for 160 yards and two touchdowns, including a 52-yarder, and Bowling Green survived a wild finish to beat Buffalo 27-19 in both teams' season finale on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bowling Green holds on to beat Buffalo in season finale

video.headline: Bowling Green holds on for last play victory

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Quarterback Kenny Hill ran for two touchdowns and TCU beat Texas 31-9 Friday, sending Longhorns coach Charlie Strong to a crushing loss in what may be his final game after three seasons.
headlines.shortLinkText: Charlie Strong and Texas soundly beaten by TCU, 31-9

events.name: Louisiana Tech Bulldogs at Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles

headlines.description: Nick Mullens threw for 342 yards and three touchdowns and sneaked in for another in his final home game as Southern Miss defeated Louisiana Tech 39-24 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mullens throws for 3 TDs; Southern Miss beats LaTech 39-24

video.headline: Robertson outjumps defender for Southern Miss TD

events.name: Baylor Bears at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Patrick Mahomes threw for 586 yards and matched his career high with six touchdown passes, including three on one-play drives before halftime, as Texas Tech finished its season with a win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes throws 6 TD passes in Texas Tech finale, 54-35 over Baylor

video.headline: Mahomes' six-TD night leads Texas Tech past Baylor

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at Tulsa Golden Hurricane
Arizona State Sun Devils at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Samajie Grant ran for 176 yards and three touchdowns, and Arizona racked up a school-record 511 yards on the ground to roll over rival Arizona State 56-35 Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arizona runs for 511 yards in 56-35 win over Arizona State
